definitions.definition: A three-dimensional work of art created by shaping malleable objects and letting them harden or by chipping away pieces from a rock ( sculpting ).
More generally (since modernism ), a three-dimensional work of art of any material or of mixed materials, whether sculpted, assembled, found, constructed or created using multiple techniques.
Works of art created by sculpting, as a group.
The three-dimensional ornamentation on the outer surface of a shell .
A printed picture , such as an engraving .
